name: google-key-management-service
label: Google Key Management Service
description: Google Key Management Service allows you to create, import, and manage cryptographic keys and perform cryptographic operations in a single centralized cloud service. This connector facilitates the automated operations related to location, keyRings, cryptoKey and cryptoKey version.

fields.title: Server URL
fields.name: server
fields.description: The service-based URI to which you will connect and perform the automated operations.

fields.title: Client ID
fields.name: client_id
fields.description: Unique Client ID of the Google Key Management Service that is used to create an authentication token required to access the Google Key Management Service API.

fields.title: Client Secret
fields.name: client_secret
fields.description: Unique Client Secret of the Google Key Management Service that is used to create an authentication token required to access the API. For information on how to get the client secret, see https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/oauth2/web-server.

fields.title: Authorization Code
fields.name: code
fields.tooltip: The authorization code that you acquired during the authorization step. For more information, see the Accessing the Google Key Management Service API section.
fields.description: The authorization code that you acquired during the authorization step. For more information, see the Accessing the Google Key Management Service API section.

fields.title: Redirect URL
fields.description: The redirect_uri of your app, where authentication responses can be sent and received by your app. It must exactly match one of the redirect_uri's you registered in the app registration portal.
fields.name: redirect_url
fields.tooltip: The redirect_uri of your app, where authentication responses can be sent and received by your app. It must exactly match one of the redirect_uri's you registered in the app registration portal.

fields.title: Verify SSL
fields.name: verify_ssl
fields.description: Specifies whether the SSL certificate for the server is to be verified or not. By default, this option is set as True.

operations.title: Create CryptoKey
operations.description: Creates a new CryptoKey within a KeyRing in Google Key Management Service based on the project ID, location ID, KeyRing ID, CrytoKey ID, and other input parameters you have specified.

parameters.title: Project ID
parameters.description: The ID of the project for which you want to create the CryptoKey in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: project_id

parameters.title: Location ID
parameters.description: The ID of the location for which you want to create the CryptoKey in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: location_id

parameters.title: KeyRing ID
parameters.description: The ID of the KeyRing in which you want to create the CryptoKey in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: key_ring_id
parameters.tooltip: Unique KeyRing ID within a location and match the regular expression [a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,63}

parameters.title: CryptoKey ID
parameters.description: The ID of the CryptoKey that you want to create in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: cryptoKeyId
parameters.tooltip: Unique cryptoKey ID within a key ring and match the regular expression [a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,63}

parameters.title: Skip Initial Version Creation
parameters.description: (Optional) Select this checkbox, if you want this request to create a CryptoKey without any CryptoKeyVersions.
parameters.name: skipInitialVersionCreation
parameters.tooltip: (Optional) Select this checkbox, if you want this request to create a CryptoKey without any CryptoKeyVersions.

parameters.title: Purpose
parameters.description: (Optional) Select the purpose of the CryptoKey that you want to create in Google Key Management Service. The CryptoKey purpose describes the cryptographic capabilities of a CryptoKey. A given key can only be used for the operations allowed by its purpose. You can choose from the following options: Symmetric Encrypt/Decrypt, Asymmetric Sign, Asymmetric Decrypt, or MAC Signing/Verification.
parameters.name: purpose

parameters.title: Next Rotation Time
parameters.description: (Optional) The DateTime of the next scheduled rotation run. At the nextRotationTime, the Key Management Service automatically creates a new version of this CryptoKey and marks the new version as primary. A timestamp or a date in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, accurate to nanoseconds is added to the CrytoKey. For example, "2014-10-02T15:01:23.045123456Z".
parameters.name: nextRotationTime
parameters.tooltip: (Optional) The DateTime of the next scheduled rotation run. At the nextRotationTime, the Key Management Service automatically creates a new version of this CryptoKey and marks the new version as primary. A timestamp or a date in RFC3339 UTC "Zulu" format, accurate to nanoseconds is added to the CrytoKey. For example, "2014-10-02T15:01:23.045123456Z".

parameters.title: Protection Level
parameters.description: (Optional) The Protection Level to use when creating the CryptoKeyVersion based on this template. You can choose from the following options: PROTECTION_LEVEL_UNSPECIFIED, SOFTWARE, HSM, or EXTERNAL.
parameters.name: protectionLevel
parameters.tooltip: (Optional) The Protection Level to use when creating the CryptoKeyVersion based on this template. You can choose from the following options: PROTECTION_LEVEL_UNSPECIFIED, SOFTWARE, HSM, or EXTERNAL.

parameters.title: Algorithm
parameters.description: (Optional) The Algorithm to use when creating the CryptoKeyVersion based on this template. You can choose from the options such as: CRYPTO_KEY_VERSION_ALGORITHM_UNSPECIFIED, GOOGLE_SYMMETRIC_ENCRYPTION, RSA_SIGN_PSS_2048_SHA256, etc.
parameters.name: algorithm
parameters.tooltip: (Optional) The Algorithm to use when creating the CryptoKeyVersion based on this template. You can choose from the options such as: CRYPTO_KEY_VERSION_ALGORITHM_UNSPECIFIED, GOOGLE_SYMMETRIC_ENCRYPTION, RSA_SIGN_PSS_2048_SHA256, etc.

parameters.title: Labels
parameters.description: (Optional) Labels with user-defined metadata that you want to apply to the CryptoKey that you want to create in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: labels

parameters.title: Rotation Period
parameters.description: (Optional) Specify the time in seconds between the automatic generation of new key versions. The rotation period must be set between 24 hours and 876,000 hours. If the rotation period is set, then the next rotation time must also be set. Keys with the purpose ENCRYPT_DECRYPT support automatic rotation. For other keys, this field must be omitted.
parameters.name: rotationPeriod
parameters.tooltip: (Optional) Specify the time in seconds between the automatic generation of new key versions. The rotation period must be set between 24 hours and 876,000 hours. If the rotation period is set, then the next rotation time must also be set. Keys with the purpose ENCRYPT_DECRYPT support automatic rotation. For other keys, this field must be omitted.

operations.title: Create CryptoKey Version
operations.description: Creates a new CryptoKey Version within a specified CryptoKey in Google Key Management Service based on the project ID, location ID, KeyRing ID, CrytoKey ID, and other input parameters you have specified.

parameters.title: Project ID
parameters.description: The ID of the project for which you want to create the CryptoKey version in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: project_id

parameters.title: Location ID
parameters.description: The ID of the location for which you want to create the CryptoKey version in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: location_id

parameters.title: KeyRing ID
parameters.description: The ID of the KeyRing in which you want to create the CryptoKey version in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: key_ring_id
parameters.tooltip: Unique KeyRing ID within a location and match the regular expression [a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,63}

parameters.title: CryptoKey ID
parameters.description: The ID of the CryptoKey for which you want to create a version in Google Key Management Service.
parameters.name: cryptoKeyId
parameters.tooltip: Unique CryptoKey ID within a key ring and match the regular expression [a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,63}

parameters.title: State
parameters.description: (Optional) Select the state of a CryptoKeyVersion, which indicates whether or not the created version can be used. You can choose from the following options: CRYPTO_KEY_VERSION_STATE_UNSPECIFIED, PENDING_GENERATION, ENABLED, DISABLED, DESTROYED, DESTROY_SCHEDULED, PENDING_IMPORT, or IMPORT_FAILED.
parameters.name: state

parameters.title: External Key URI
parameters.description: (Optional) The URI of an external resource that represents this CryptoKeyVersion.
parameters.name: externalKeyUri
